import subprocess
import sys
import ctypes

try:
    import fitz
except ImportError:
    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, "-m", "pip", "install", 'pymupdf'])
finally:
    import fitz
    
### READ IN PDF
def AddSignFieldInPDF(InputData):
    lstInputData = InputData.split("|")
    doc = fitz.open(lstInputData[0])
    page = doc[0]

    ### SEARCH

    startPosition = page.searchFor("for Jabra Connect India Pvt Ltd")
    endPosition = page.searchFor("Authorised Signatory")

    ### Set Signature Position

    widget = fitz.Widget()
    widget.rect = fitz.Rect(startPosition[0].x0,startPosition[0].y0+startPosition[0].y1-startPosition[0].y0,startPosition[0].x1,endPosition[0].y0)
    widget.field_type = fitz.PDF_WIDGET_TYPE_SIGNATURE
    widget.field_name = "DigitalSign"
    page.addWidget(widget)

    ### OUTPUT

    doc.save(lstInputData[1], garbage=4, deflate=True, clean=True)

    ### Get Screen Resolution
    user32 = ctypes.windll.user32
    screensize = str(user32.GetSystemMetrics(0)) + "," + str(user32.GetSystemMetrics(1))
    return screensize
